# UI Design Style

## Color Palette

Use the predefined color variables in the color system:

```typescript
// Primary colors
--canteen-teal: #00A896    // Main brand color
--canteen-mint: #8FE1D7    // Light accent 
--canteen-yellow: #F9C80E  // Secondary accent
--canteen-coral: #FF5E5B   // Alert/error
--canteen-dark: #1c2536    // Text/dark backgrounds
--canteen-lightgray: #F2F7F9 // Light backgrounds
--canteen-darkgray: #5A6876 // Subtle text/icons
```

Use CSS variables for theming support:
- Light mode: Use directly from the palette
- Dark mode: Use the CSS variables with `dark:` prefix

## Typography

- Font family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif
- Base text size: 0.925rem
- Use the typography scale:
  - Headings: font-bold
  - Body: font-normal or font-medium
  - Buttons: font-medium

## Components & Styling

### Buttons

Use predefined button styles:

```tsx
// Primary button (teal)
<Button className="bg-gradient-to-r from-canteen-teal to-canteen-mint dark:from-primary dark:to-canteen-mint hover:opacity-90 text-white rounded-full shadow-md">
  Button Text
</Button>

// Secondary button (yellow)
<Button variant="secondary" className="bg-canteen-yellow text-canteen-dark hover:opacity-90">
  Button Text
</Button>

// Ghost/icon button
<Button variant="ghost" size="icon" className="rounded-full text-canteen-darkgray dark:text-gray-400 hover:text-canteen-teal">
  <Icon size={18} />
</Button>
```

### Cards

```tsx
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-card rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-100 dark:border-primary/10 card-hover">
  {/* Optional highlight at top */}
  <div className="card-header-highlight">
    {/* Card content */}
  </div>
</div>
```

### Animations

Use the animation utility classes:
- `animate-float` - Gentle floating animation
- `animate-pulse-subtle` - Subtle pulsing effect
- `animate-fade-in-up` - Fade in from bottom
- `page-transition-wrapper` - Page transition

Add delay variations with:
- `delay-100`, `delay-200`, etc.

### Icons

- Use Lucide React icons
- Default size: 18px for UI elements
- Keep consistent with the overall design language

## Layout & Spacing

- Use the container class for consistent width
- Use Tailwind's spacing scale: `px-4 py-2 m-3 gap-2`
- For main sections, use `section` tag with padding: `py-12 md:py-16`
- Modal padding: `p-6`
- Card padding: `p-4`

## Visual Effects

- Gradients: Use for emphasis, buttons, and branding elements
- Shadows: Light shadows for cards and interactive elements
- Transitions: Include transition properties for hover/interactive states
  - `transition-all duration-300`

## Dark Mode Support

Ensure all UI components support dark mode using Tailwind's dark mode variant:

```tsx
<div className="bg-white text-canteen-dark dark:bg-card dark:text-white">
  {/* Component content */}
</div>
```

## Responsive Design

- Use mobile-first approach
- Breakpoints: sm, md, lg, xl, 2xl
- Common patterns:
  - Hidden on mobile, visible on desktop: `hidden md:flex`
  - Different layouts: `flex-col md:flex-row`

## Accessibility

- Maintain color contrast (WCAG AA minimum)
- Include aria labels for interactive elements
- Support keyboard navigation
- Ensure focus states are visible